cly that cultural patronage of and exchange with Israel advanced America's interests in the Middle East and helped spread the "American way" in the postwar world. Bringing Zion Home is the first book to shine a light squarely upon the role and importance of Israel in the arts, popular culture, and material culture of postwar America.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aIsrael and the diaspora. 0aJewszUnited StatesxAttitudes toward Israel. 0aJewszUnited StatesxSocial life and customsy20th century. 0aPublic opinionzUnited States. 4aArea Studies : Israel Studies. 4aHistory : American History. 4aHistory : History. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : American Religion. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Jewish Studies.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845466540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438454665423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438454665/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles